        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 8:22PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Moore, or 14 miles west of Lewistown, moving northeast at 40 mph
with additional storms along a line extending north to near
Winifred. A period of moderate to heavy rainfall and lightning is
accompanying these storms with hail to to one half inch possible
near the stronger cell tracking northeast of Moore.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Hobson, Winifred, Moore, Roy, Fergus, Forestgrove,
Glengarry, Garneill, Danvers, Suffolk, Giltedge, Heath, Hilger, and
Christina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
